
                                   EyeDB examples README


EyeDB examples are organized in 3 directories:
- GettingStarted/ : self-contained simple example with a schema, C++ and Java code
- C++Binding/ : examples using the EyeDB C++ API
- JavaBinding/ : examples using the EyeDB Java API


GettingStarted
==============

This directory contains a simple schema and two simple programs 
using the EyEDB C++ and Java APIs.

To run the C++ and Java examples in the GettingStarted/ directory:

1) compile them with 'make check'

2) run the init.sh script with 'make init'
This script creates the database 'person_g' and insert a few objects.
NOTE: this must be done only once.

3) run the 'persontest' C++ program with:
./persontest person_g

4) run the 'PersonTest Java program using the eyedbjrun script:
CLASSPATH=. eyedbjrun PersonTest person_g

5) check the database using eyedboql:
% eyedboql -d person_g
? select Person->lastname;
bag(NULL, NULL, NULL, "poppins", "poppins", "travolta", "stuart", "baby5", "wayne", "wayne", "baby4", "baby2", "baby3", "baby1")
? select Person->firstname;
= bag("baby5", "baby4", "john", "john", "john", "mary", "mary", "mary", "baby2", "baby2", "baby3", "baby3", "baby1", "baby1")
? \quit
%


C++Binding
==========

This directory contains C++ programs that use the EyEDB C++ API.
This API is described in EyeDB 'C++ Binding' manual.

To run the C++ examples in the C++Binding/ directory:

1) compile them with 'make check'

2) run the init.sh script located in C++Binding/schema-oriented/share
with 'make init'
This script creates the database 'person_c' and insert a few objects.
NOTE: this must be done only once.

3) run the programs

To run the examples, cd to the following directories and
run the indicated command:

DIRECTORY               COMMANDS
-------------------------------------------------------
generic/query           ./query person "select Person"
                        ./query person "select Person.name ~ \"j\""
                        ./query person "select Person.age"
-------------------------------------------------------
generic/store           ./store person raymon 32
                        ./store person titou 2
-------------------------------------------------------
schema-oriented/query   ./query person "select Person"
                        ./query person "select Person.name ~ \"j\""
-------------------------------------------------------
schema-oriented/store   ./store person nadine 32 raymond
-------------------------------------------------------
schema-oriented/methods ./methods person john 12
                         NOTE THAT for this directory, you need to copy
                         the *.so files to EyeDB dynamic objects directory:
                         cp *.so $EYEDBROOT/etc/so
-------------------------------------------------------
schema-oriented/admin   ./admin
-------------------------------------------------------


JavaBinding
===========

EyeDB Package, Java Binding examples
------------------------------------

[Directory $EYEDBROOT/examples/JavaBinding]

This directory contains a few examples about Java binding.

To compile the examples in this directory, you must:

(1) Then type `make init' and `make all' in the current directory 
    using GNU make.

(2) To run the generated example, go to the following directories and
    perform the indicated actions:

DIRECTORY                   RUNNING EXAMPLES
--------------------------------------------------------------
generic/appli/basic       eyedbjrun Basic person
----------------------------------------------------------------
generic/appli/query       eyedbjrun Query person <any valid query>
                          for instance:
                          eyedbjrun Query person "select Person"
----------------------------------------------------------------
generic/appli/store       eyedbjrun Store person <name> <age>
----------------------------------------------------------------
generic/appli/collections eyedbjrun Collections person <prefix>
----------------------------------------------------------------
generic/appli/schema      eyedbjrun Store person
----------------------------------------------------------------
generic/applet            with Netscape, open the applet.html page
----------------------------------------------------------------
